<!--
    HSK patch: gate Wolfein MegaCorp raids by replacing the
    raidCommonalityFromPointsCurve so they don't appear in early-game /
    low-wealth / tribal scenarios.

    Why?
    Wolfein_Faction_MegaCorp is a Spacer-tier corporate faction whose
    pawnGroupMakers include custom Wolfein mechanoids (MilitaryA/B/D +
    armed drones) plus regional supervisors. Their default
    raidCommonalityFromPointsCurve was just `(0, 1)` — a single point
    meaning full weight at ANY raid budget. Result: same problem as
    pre-fix Junker pirates / VFE Mechanoids — early-game tribal colony
    can be raided by spacer-tier mecha-corps on day 4.

    Fix: replace the curve with a step-function that gates raids below
    2000 raid points (~100k+ wealth, very late game). MegaCorp is the
    HIGHEST-tier Wolfein threat — corporate execs with private mechanoid
    armies — so the threshold is higher than the 1500 used for vanilla
    VFE Mechanoids. Player needs charge weapons + EMP + Plasteel armor
    before this faction can pick them as a target.

    Replacement curve:
        (0, 0)         — no raids at any low budget
        (1999, 0)      — still 0 right up to the threshold
        (2000, 0.001)  — barely above 0 at the threshold (sharp step)
        (3500, 1)      — full normal weight at very late game
        (5000, 1.5)    — slightly higher weight at endgame

    The (1999, 0) -> (2000, 0.001) step is intentional — produces an
    effectively step-function gate while keeping the curve interpolation
    valid (RimWorld curves require monotonic-x).

    Wolfein_Faction_Rebel is NOT gated — it's a hidden permanent-enemy
    faction driven by quest scripts, not the storyteller's normal raid
    roster. Quest-driven encounters bypass this curve.

    Mirrors the raid-gating pattern from HSK-VFE-Pirates (Junker),
    HSK-VFE-Mechanoids, and HSK-VFE-Insectoid2.
-->
<Patch>

    <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
        <xpath>Defs/FactionDef[defName="Wolfein_Faction_MegaCorp"]/raidCommonalityFromPointsCurve</xpath>
        <value>
            <raidCommonalityFromPointsCurve>
                <points>
                    <li>(0, 0)</li>
                    <li>(1999, 0)</li>
                    <li>(2000, 0.001)</li>
                    <li>(3500, 1)</li>
                    <li>(5000, 1.5)</li>
                </points>
            </raidCommonalityFromPointsCurve>
        </value>
    </Operation>

</Patch>
